Olympic Acronyms

Midlet created with Sun J2ME Wireless Toolkit 2.2 [patch 200508].

o How to build:

  - extract to the j2mewt "apps" directory
  - run ktoolbar from j2mewt "bin" directory and open Olympic Acronyms Project,
    click on Project menu and then Package, Create Package

    or type these commands from Olympic Acronyms directory:

    [in Linux]
    - javac -bootclasspath ../../lib/cldcapi10.jar:../../lib/midpapi10.jar -d tmpclasses src/*.java
    - ../../bin/preverify -classpath ../../lib/cldcapi10.jar:../../lib/midpapi10.jar -d classes tmpclasses
    - jar cfm bin/OlympicAcronyms.jar MANIFEST.MF -C classes . -C res .

    [in Windows]
    - javac -bootclasspath ..\..\lib\cldcapi10.jar;..\..\lib\midpapi10.jar -d tmpclasses src\*.java
    - ..\..\bin\preverify -classpath ..\..\lib\cldcapi10.jar;..\..\lib\midpapi10.jar -d classes tmpclasses
    - jar cfm bin\OlympicAcronyms.jar MANIFEST.MF -C classes . -C res .

o How to try:

  click on ktoolbar "Run" button
  or run emulator from j2mewt "bin" directory (the JAD file must be created)

o How to send midlet to phone:

  use Bluetooth
  or IrDA
  or serial/USB cable

